# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Local development (recommended)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Use the Firebase emulator instead of real Firebase credentials.
# No setup required — fake values are already in .env.emulator.
#
#   Terminal 1: pnpm --filter @bookbingo/web emulator:start
#   Terminal 2: pnpm run dev:web:emulator
#   Seed data:  pnpm --filter @bookbingo/web emulator:seed
#
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Real Firebase project (staging / prod)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Copy this file to .env.staging or .env.prod and fill in real values.
VITE_FIREBASE_API_KEY=your-api-key
VITE_FIREBASE_AUTH_DOMAIN=your-project.firebaseapp.com
VITE_FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID=your-project-id
VITE_FIREBASE_STORAGE_BUCKET=your-project.appspot.com
VITE_FIREBASE_MESSAGING_SENDER_ID=your-sender-id
VITE_FIREBASE_APP_ID=your-app-id
VITE_FIREBASE_MEASUREMENT_ID=G-XXXXXXXXXX
